uniol.apt.adt

Class AbstractGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.adt.extension.Extensible
      • uniol.apt.adt.AbstractGraph<G,E,N>
  • Type Parameters:
    G - The type of the graph itself.
    E - The type of the edges.
    N - The type of the nodes.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IExtensible, IGraph<G,E,N>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PetriNet, TransitionSystem

    public abstract class AbstractGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
extends Extensible
implements IGraph<G,E,N>
    AbstractGraph is an abstract implementation of the IGraph interface. It extends Extensible and adds an implementation of the listener methods. To invoke listeners, the invokeListeners method can be called.
    Author:
    Uli Schlachter
